criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with 18 years of age and older;

          -  Ability to provide free and informed consent before entering the study;

          -  Imaging diagnosis of a solid pancreatic lesion that was proposed for EUS
             characterization;

          -  Presence of sectional imaging method (CT/MRI) performed within six months before
             randomization;

          -  Blood test (blood count and coagulation studies) compatible with the performance of
             invasive maneuvers;

          -  Clinical indication by the endoscopist for EUS-tissue acquisition with the use of an
             FNB needle.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Failure to provide free and informed consent;

          -  Clinically significant change in haemostasis laboratory parameters: International
             Normalized Ratio (INR) > 1.5; activated partial thromboplastin time (aPTT)> 50
             seconds; Platelets <50,000;

          -  Absence of a proper anticoagulant and/or anti-aggregate therapy discontinuation for
             the performance of FNB;

          -  Absence of fasting (2h without clear liquids and 6h without solid foods);

          -  Clinical suspicion of upper digestive tract obstruction;

          -  An episode of acute pancreatitis within four weeks before echoendoscopy;

          -  Respiratory failure or hemodynamic instability;

          -  Pregnancy or breast-feeding.
